data.description: Come see this mid-century modern home in the beautiful hamlet of Livingston Manor.  This 3 possibly 4 bedroom, two bath home boasts! Over 1,900 sq ft of living space.  A short distance to town boasting an array of amenities including The Livingston Manor Fly Fishing Club and The Catskill Fly Fishing Museum,The The Arnold House, The DeBruce, The Catskill Brewery, Upward Brewery, and the classic The Robin Hood Diner.  Come see this wonderful downtown.   There are multiple parks in the area including Covered Bridge Park and Rotary Park where there is ice skating in the winter, when it's cold enough.  Come live here and enjoy it all.  Can be a short term rental, town has regulations and registration.  Pre-approval and/or proof of funds required for showing.
